s against you equal to your Charisma bonus. You can gain this benefit against only one foes at a time; it lasts until the encounter ends or you switch targets. This can't work on mindless creatures or those immune to fear.
Einhander				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Tactical.Fighter	VISIBLE:YES																																																																PRESKILL:1,Tumble=6																														DESC:You excel at wielding a one-handed weapon while carrying nothing in your off hand.																																	MULT:NO																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.94																BENEFIT:Gain 3 maneuvers which require wielding a one handed weapon and having an empty off hand. Narrow Profile - You tuck your off hand behind your back and offer a narrow profile when fighting defensively. This adds and additional dodge bonus of +2 AC.  Off-hand Balance - YOu use your off hand to balance yourself while performing acrobatic maneuvers. After you successfully strike an opponent, you gain a +2 bonus on Tumble checks to avoid his attacks of opportunity until the start of your next turn.  Off-Hand Swap - With a flourish, you flip your weapon into the air and catch it in your off hand, and continue to press the attack. You start this maneuver by taking a full attack action to strike an opponent at least twice. On round 2, you can make a special feint as a free action, using Sleight of Hand rather than Bluff. You opponent uses the standard rules for resisting a feint. Once you use this maneuver against a particular opponent, whether it succeeds or fails, you cannot use it on him again.																																																																																																																																																							PRETOTALAB:6
Mad Alchemist			CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Tactical		VISIBLE:YES																				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Grenadier																																									PRESKILL:1,Craft (Alchemy)=6																													DESC:You are an expert at using alchemical items. Through experimentation, research, and your careful study of the art of alchemy, you have learned to make the most of items such as alchemist's fire.																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.94																BENEFIT:Gain 3 maneuvers. Distracting Blast - If you ready an action to throw a thunderstone at the square an opponent occupies, you can disrupt his actions. The sudden bang from the stone's detonation ruins your foe's concentration, possibly spoiling his attack or spell. If the target of the blast was casting a spell, he must make a Concentration check opposed by your Craft (Alchemy) check. If you succeed, his spell is ruined. If the target was not casting a spell, he makes a Will save vs. your check or takes a -2 penalty on attack rolls, checks, and saves until the beginning of your next turn.  Fiery Blaze - To use this maneuver you strike an opponent with lantern oil or alchemist's fire. On round 2 you strike the creature with a spell or weapon dealing fire damage. If you do so, the creature takes an extra 1d6 points of fire damage and catches fire if not already in flames.  Tanglefoot Defense - By tearing open a tanglefoot bag and spreading its contents across an area, you can create a vexing barrier that hinders an opponent's approach. As a standard action, you can transform a single square of clear terrain into difficult terrain. This effect persists for 10 minutes before the tanglefoot bag loses its potency.
Shadow Striker			CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Tactical.Fighter	VISIBLE:YES																																																																PRESKILL:2,Hide=12,Move Silently=12																												DESC:You melt into the shadows, hiding from your enemies until the time is right. Your cunning, guile, and stealth allow you to pick the most opportune moment to strike.																			MULT:NO																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.94																BENEFIT:Gain 3 maneuvers. Evade Notice - If both you and an ally threaten an opponent, you can attempt to slip beneath your opponent's notice. On your turn, if you take no hostile actions, such as attacking, casting an offensive spell, and so forth, you may make a Hide check opposed by the foe's SPot check. If you succeed, your foe cannot attack you on his next turn as long as he threatens another active opponent. If you attack your foe for any reason before or during his next turn, you lose this maneuver's benefit.  Fade Away - In round 1 you make an attack as a standard action, then move away and attempt a Hide as part of your move action for the turn. If you attack hits, you get a +5 bonus on your Hide check.  Ghost Strike - You use an ally's distraction and your talent to move noiselessly and slip out of your oppenent's field of vision for a single, crucial moment. To use this maneuver, both you and an ally must threaten a foe. As a standard action, you make a Move Silently check opposed by your foe's Listen check. If you succeed on this check, you gain this maneuver's benefit. On the next round, your target loses his Dexterity bonus to AC against your first attack of the round so long as both you and your ally still threaten him.
